<%- layout('layouts/boilerplate')  %>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/home.css" />
</head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <section>
        <div id="bg-image"></div>
        <div id="header-text">
          <h1>Welcome To Track</h1>
          <p>
            The All-in-one tool to take your productivity to the next level!
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <img
          class="img-fluid"
          id="app-screenshot"
          src="assets/image13.webp"
          alt="app screenshot"
        />
      </section>
      <section class="mt-3">
        <ul class="row">
          <li class="col">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-bolt"></i> Fast & Responsive
          </li>
          <li class="col">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-dollar-sign"></i> Free to Use
          </li>
          <li class="col">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-fingerprint"></i> Fully Personalized
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </header>
    <main>
      <section id="mid-section-text">
        <h2>
          Journaling your goals, <br />
          brings you closer to them
        </h2>
      </section>
      <section id="collapse-menu" class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <article class="col-6">
            <p>
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nulla quo
              commodi nesciunt expedita at magnam pariatur aperiam, voluptatibus
              earum modi quia soluta labore accusantium, excepturi incidunt quis
              aliquid iure! Est!
            </p>
          </article>
          <article id="accordion" class="col-6">
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header" id="headingOne">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button
                    class="btn"
                    data-toggle="collapse"
                    data-target="#collapseOne"
                    aria-expanded="true"
                    aria-controls="collapseOne"
                  >
                    The Importance of Planning
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>

              <div
                id="collapseOne"
                class="collapse show"
                aria-labelledby="headingOne"
              >
                <div class="card-body" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <p>
                    Planning decreases the chances of risk: Planning is an
                    activity which permits a manager to look forward and predict
                    changes. By determining in prior the tasks to be completed,
                    planning notes the way to deal with changes and
                    unpredictable effects.
                  </p>
                  <h4>
                    It helps us achieve our goals, and allows for more efficient
                    use of time and other resources.
                  </h4>
                  <ul>
                    <h6>Not planning leads to:</h6>
                    <li>Wasted resources</li>
                    <li>Unpredictable results</li>
                    <li>Less oppurtunity for cooperation</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
                <h5 class="mb-0">
                  <button
                    class="btn"
                    data-toggle="collapse"
                    data-target="#collapseTwo"
                    aria-expanded="true"
                    aria-controls="collapseTwo"
                  >
                    The Curse of Overplanning
                  </button>
                </h5>
              </div>

              <div
                id="collapseTwo"
                class="collapse show"
                aria-labelledby="headingTwo"
              >
                <div class="card-body" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <p>
                    Excessive planning can lead to anxiety, disappointment,
                    stunted creativity, lack of trust and scattered focus. I
                    also have seen “overplanning” actually hinder performance
                    and limit success.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    If you have multiple forms of planning and update all of
                    them regularly that means a chunk of your time is going to
                    simply planning out your actions. Are you actually getting
                    those things done?
                  </p>
                  <h4>It's a form of procrastination</h4>
                  <img
                    class="img-fluid"
                    src="assets/936q8cqzvn6a1.webp"
                    alt="overplanning image"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </header>
  </body>
</html>
